# Carbon Counter Workspace Rules

## Design Philosophy
- Proactively suggest modern design trends
- Focus on immersive user experience
- Implement latest web design practices
- Balance aesthetics with functionality
- Prioritize performance and accessibility

## 2024/2025 Design Standards
### Visual Design
- Glassmorphism for cards
- Micro-interactions
- Dark mode optimized
- Subtle gradients
- Variable fonts
- 3D elements where appropriate

### Interactive Elements
- Smooth scroll behaviors
- Gesture-based interactions
- Progressive loading
- Skeleton screens
- Dynamic tooltips
- Scroll-triggered animations

### Layout Principles
- Grid-based layouts
- Whitespace utilization
- Responsive breakpoints
- Container queries
- Fluid typography
- Vertical rhythm

## Project-Specific Guidelines

### Color System
```css
Primary: #0B1321 (Dark blue)
Secondary: #1A2332 (Light blue)
Accent: #4AE290 (Green)
Text: #ffffff
```

### Typography
- System fonts for performance
- Fluid type scaling
- Minimum 16px base
- Clear hierarchy
- Optimal line length

### Components
- Reusable card structure
- Consistent spacing
- Interactive states
- Loading states
- Error states

### Data Visualization
- Real-time updates
- Smooth transitions
- Clear data labels
- Mobile-optimized views
- Accessible colors

## Development Approach

### Performance
- Lazy loading
- Code splitting
- Asset optimization
- Cache strategies
- Performance budgets

### Accessibility
- WCAG 2.1 compliance
- Keyboard navigation
- Screen reader support
- Color contrast
- Focus management

### SEO
- Semantic structure
- Meta optimization
- Schema markup
- Performance metrics
- Mobile optimization

## AI Assistant Role
- Suggest modern alternatives
- Point out dated practices
- Recommend performance improvements
- Share industry best practices
- Provide trend-aware solutions

## Implementation Rules
### Before Changes
- Suggest modern alternatives
- Consider mobile impact
- Check performance implications
- Verify accessibility

### During Development
- Progressive enhancement
- Browser compatibility
- Performance monitoring
- Responsive testing

### After Implementation
- Verify best practices
- Check against trends
- Test cross-browser
- Validate accessibility

## Project Structure
```
/static
  /css
    - styles.css (main styles)
    - variables.css (design tokens)
    - components.css (reusable components)
  /js
    - main.js (core functionality)
    - counters.js (counter logic)
    - animations.js (animation controls)
  /images
    - optimized and properly sized
  /data
    - emissions-data.json
    - country-data.json
```

## Git Commit Standards
- feat: New feature addition
- fix: Bug fixes
- style: Visual updates
- perf: Performance improvements
- docs: Documentation updates
- refactor: Code restructuring

## Quality Checklist
- Mobile-first approach verified
- Cross-browser compatibility tested
- Performance metrics checked
- Accessibility guidelines followed
- SEO best practices implemented
- Modern design patterns used
- Documentation updated
- Code optimization completed


verify that you understand me before making any changes.
*These rules serve as a living document and can be updated as new trends and best practices emerge in web development.*
